ain from alcohol, hard drugs, or even dangerous and physically addictive prescription drugs! It is also being established that Cannabis use may help prevent such serious illnesses as cancer and Alzheimer's disease! Cannabis use also suppresses violent urges and behaviors. Let's not be intimidated by the scare-tactics of the "opponents", but be motivated instead by science, reason and understanding of these issues, and this means voting YES on California Proposition 19 on November 2!</dd> <dd class="tool clearfix"> <!-- assetVote: --> <!-- logged in: --> <!-- remember me: --> <a class="reply needsReg">Reply to this comment</a> <a class="mail toolTipElement2 needsReg" title="E-mail to a friend"></a> <a class="repo toolTipElement2 needsReg" title="Report offensive content"></a> <a class="link toolTipElement2" href="/8618-18567_162-4828659.html?assetTypeId=30&messageId=9813295" title="Permalink to this comment"></a> </dd> <dd class="toolstretch"><!-- --></dd> </dl> <!-- --> <a name="9768445"></a> <dl messageid="9768445"> <dt class="subj"></dt> <dt class="author"> <span>by <b>karika1999</b></span> August 21, 2010 3:11 PM EDT </dt> <dd id="body_9768445">I do not drink. I do like to smoke cannabis. I have migraines, arthritis and other pain issues. I could go get a med card, but I do not use medical doctors. I just want to be able to grow my own plants and use them for pain, anxiety and appetite stimulant. I await the day I can do it legally, until then, I live with the pain. I have read what LEAP (Law Enforcement Against Prohibition) has to say about the subject and I am pleased progress is being made to educate others. We could save so much money as a nation if we stop punishing people for their lifestyle choices that do not hurt others. No one has ever died of a cannabis overdose, yet many thousands die from pharmaceutical drugs yearly.</dd> <dd class="tool clearfix"> <!-- assetVote: --> <!-- logged in: --> <!-- remember me: --> <a class="reply needsReg">Reply to this c